-- 
-- Wed Apr 02, 2014 06:58AM EDT
-- None



April 2 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several Canadian companies, including and Bell Aliant Inc, on Wednesday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Bell Aliant Inc <BA.TO>: Barclays cuts to underweight from equal weight rating * Imperial Oil Ltd <IMO.TO>: RBC, Canaccord Genuity raise target price * Nordion <NDZ.N>: Canaccord Genuity cuts to hold from buy rating  Following is a summary of research actions on Canadian companies reported by Reuters on Wednesday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* Amaya Gaming Group <AYA.TO>: Canaccord Genuity cuts target to C$8.75 from C$10; rating buy * Bell Aliant Inc <BA.TO>: Barclays cuts to underweight from equal weight rating * Cardinal Energy <CJ.TO>: CIBC raises target price to c$17.25 from c$16.50 * Imperial Oil Ltd <IMO.TO>: RBC raises target to C$52 from C$51; rating sector perform * Imperial Oil Ltd <IMO.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target price to C$49; rating hold * Imperial Oil Ltd <IMO.TO>: RBC raises target to c$52 from c$51; rating sector perform * Input Capital Corp <INP.V>: Canaccord Genuity raises target to C$3 from C$2.75; rating buy * MAG Silver Corp <MAG.TO>: Scotia capital starts with outperform - Theflyonthewall.com * Morguard Corp <MRC.TO>: RBC raises target price to c$150 from c$145; rating outperform * Nordion <NDZ.N>: Canaccord Genuity cuts to hold from buy rating * Partners Reit <PAR_u.TO>: RBC cuts to underperform; cuts target to c$5.50 from c$6.50 * Verde Potash PLC <NPK.TO>: Paradigm Capital raises to buy from speculative buy